ConocoPhillips Borger Oil Refinery Reports Process Upset

-- B y   A a r o n   C l a r k
-- 
2011-04-13T13:35:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/conocophillips-borger-oil-refinery-reports-process-upset-1-.html
ConocoPhillips (COP)  reported a process
upset at its Borger refinery in Texas yesterday, according to a
filing with state regulators.  Feed was sent to other equipment, according to the filing
with the Texas Commission on Environmental Quality. Emissions
associated with the incident occurred between 9:18 a.m. and 1:08
p.m. local time.  The refinery operates a 25,000-barrel-a-day coker and
processes mostly medium sour crude, according to the companyâ€™s
 website . ConocoPhillips operates a 10-inch crude pipeline, with
the capacity of 59,000 barrels a day, to Cushing, Oklahoma, from
the Borger refinery.  The refinery has a daily capacity of 154,000 barrels,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
